Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.85,0:00:02.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name's Conan Edogawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.48,0:00:05.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,High school student Shinichi was\Nforced to take a drug that shrunk him!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.65,0:00:08.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the organization learned that\NShinichi and Conan are the same person
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.44,0:00:10.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,everyone close to\Nme would be in danger!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.37,0:00:12.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only Professor Agasa\Nknows the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.62,0:00:15.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With my identity hidden,\Nthere's always only one truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.74,0:00:21.19,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The first end of the century in 100 years{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.83,0:00:27.41,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When told to cry, I laughed instead{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.03,0:00:39.50,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The first end of the century\Nin a long, long time{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.18,0:00:45.59,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We're leaping into a wide open world{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.17,0:00:52.18,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The things I tried to\Nunderstand as a child{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.34,0:00:58.61,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}remain a mystery even as an adult{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.89,0:01:04.61,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm neither a hotshot\Nnor especially great{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.89,0:01:11.03,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All I understand is\Nthe pounding of my heart{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.19,0:01:16.92,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's neither an answer nor the truth{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.20,0:01:23.00,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All I have faith in is\Nthe pounding of my heart{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.29,0:01:28.51,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That and nothing else {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.50,0:01:50.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Computer Murder Case.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.63,0:01:59.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was a good movie, huh, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.80,0:02:00.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.01,0:02:03.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hungry, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.60,0:02:05.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is it this late already?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.89,0:02:07.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's eat somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.23,0:02:10.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's eat there!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.52,0:02:13.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you insane?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.32,0:02:18.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'd cost an arm and\Na leg to eat sushi in Ginza!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.57,0:02:21.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you! Come again!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.83,0:02:25.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tonight's the night for drinking!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.54,0:02:27.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please take your medicine, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.71,0:02:29.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your heart might\Nact up again if you don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.67,0:02:32.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know, I know!\NYou sound like my wife!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.76,0:02:44.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like he's the\Npresident of a company...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.64,0:02:47.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I've seen him\Nbefore in some magazines...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.23,0:02:51.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah! He's Mr. Okida,\Npresident of Bigwood!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.48,0:02:54.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bigwood? The software company?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.02,0:02:57.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today's contract sure was big!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.69,0:03:03.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it's all thanks to the software\Nyou gave me a year ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.28,0:03:05.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I really must thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.87,0:03:12.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.00,0:03:17.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You dropped this!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.71,0:03:19.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, little boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.34,0:03:24.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tokito! Why the hell\Nweren't you paying attention?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.97,0:03:27.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry! I apologize, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.68,0:03:34.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to thank you in some way.\NWhat would you like, little boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.36,0:03:38.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon my rudeness,\Nbut aren't you Mr. Okida of Bigwood?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.11,0:03:39.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is who I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.74,0:03:43.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Private investigator Mori Kogoro...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.70,0:03:48.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! We don't need anything in return;
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.08,0:03:50.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,just let me know if you\Never need my services!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.96,0:03:53.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.83,0:03:55.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I must be going now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.21,0:03:58.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take care!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.59,0:04:02.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A private investigator, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.59,0:04:05.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to\Ndrink like a fish tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.39,0:04:14.81,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Okida
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.64,0:04:54.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori Detective Agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.56,0:04:58.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Inspector Megure!\NGood morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.69,0:05:00.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Okida's dead?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.94,0:05:07.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Inspector Megure\Nsaw your business card
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.99,0:05:09.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in Mr. Okida's suit pocket and--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.37,0:05:13.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, and then\Nhe called just to be safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.79,0:05:16.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, if the Inspector is there,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.04,0:05:17.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,does that mean someone killed him?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.79,0:05:22.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes the police\Ninvestigate unnatural deaths too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.55,0:05:24.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Okida was an\Nimportant person, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.48,0:05:39.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, you were\Nwith Mr. Okida last night...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.31,0:05:41.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Miura, his secretary!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.73,0:05:43.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.77,0:05:48.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It opened by itself!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.95,0:05:52.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did you do that?\NThat was amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.79,0:05:56.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The computer checked my\Nfingerprints and then opened the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.37,0:05:58.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Computer?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.62,0:06:01.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is an ultramodern house;
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.63,0:06:05.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,nearly everything inside\Nit is controlled by computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.89,0:06:17.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's cool in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.73,0:06:21.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The air conditioning is\Nprogrammed to always keep the place
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.81,0:06:24.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at the most pleasant\Ntemperature 24 hours a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.65,0:06:28.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Mori-{\i1}kun{\i0}! Thanks for coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.24,0:06:28.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.82,0:06:30.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.07,0:06:33.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. I told them to stay home, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.53,0:06:36.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We saw Okida-{\i1}san {\i0}last night too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.37,0:06:40.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure.\NThis is his secretary, Miura-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.79,0:06:42.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.79,0:06:46.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Tokito here discovered the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.13,0:06:49.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He came to pick\Nup Mr. Okida at 8:00,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.05,0:06:54.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he never came out, so he\Ngrew suspicious and came inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.43,0:06:58.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,only to find him cold in his bed,\Nwith his pajamas still on.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.43,0:07:01.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was the cause of death?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.44,0:07:05.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't say for sure\Nwithout a proper autopsy,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.15,0:07:07.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it was probably a sudden\Ndeath due to a heart attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.44,0:07:08.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A sudden death?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.94,0:07:14.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to his doctor,\Nhe's always had heart problems...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.07,0:07:17.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On top of that, I'm told he\Ndrank a lot of alcohol last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.08,0:07:21.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yesterday was special, as he\Nhad gotten an important contract.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.58,0:07:25.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His wife said no alcohol, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.63,0:07:27.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is his wife, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.84,0:07:32.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She left with their daughter\Non an overseas trip yesterday evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.43,0:07:36.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Last night, he went to\Na number of buyers' clubs,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.64,0:07:41.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and when he came home,\Nhe was so drunk he couldn't walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.77,0:07:46.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I took him to his\Nbedroom and put him to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.57,0:07:50.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The estimated time of death\Nwas around 2:00 a.m.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.40,0:07:53.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm asking just to be sure,\Nbut where were you then?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.62,0:07:57.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I returned to my apartment after 1:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.70,0:08:02.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At around 2:00 I bought dinner\Nat a nearby convenience store.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.12,0:08:07.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I dropped an egg at the register,\Nso I'm sure the cashier can vouch for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.26,0:08:17.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How cute! It's a Himalayan!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.60,0:08:22.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's Aslan.\NIt's the daughter's cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.94,0:08:28.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He seems hungry.\NI'll go feed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.70,0:08:36.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector. I'd like to\Nsee the body for myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.49,0:08:39.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's fine, but you two can't come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.66,0:08:41.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd pass even if\Nyou told me to look!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.00,0:08:45.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.21,0:08:51.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No exterior injuries,\Nand no sign of drugs?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.13,0:08:54.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why was he sweating so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.22,0:08:57.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look how damp he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.47,0:08:59.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sheet too!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.01,0:09:02.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For someone who died while\Nsweating, there's too much here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.43,0:09:04.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When did you get in here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.19,0:09:07.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The AC in this house\Nis computer-controlled
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.86,0:09:11.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so that the temperature\Nis always nice, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.28,0:09:13.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So then why?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.15,0:09:16.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were told to stay out!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.20,0:09:18.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get out!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.67,0:09:27.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.34,0:09:31.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The flowers are wilted.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.39,0:09:41.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The flower store receipt...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.77,0:09:44.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's from yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.64,0:09:46.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His wife probably bought\Nthem before leaving...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.02,0:09:52.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been less than a day.\NWhy are they so wilted?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.65,0:09:59.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The chocolate melted into a lump...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.16,0:10:07.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you like cats, little boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.67,0:10:08.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.75,0:10:12.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Mr. Okida\Nliked Tokito-{\i1}san{\i0}, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.46,0:10:14.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He made him his driver\Neven though he's young.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.59,0:10:18.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, he's actually a programmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.80,0:10:23.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was originally\Na programmer for our company.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.39,0:10:27.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He and a friend started a\Nsoftware company two years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.48,0:10:29.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it didn't go so well...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.90,0:10:33.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As expected, he went\Nbankrupt a year later.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.52,0:10:37.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Six months ago,\Nhe apologized to Mr. Okida
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.44,0:10:41.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and begged for another job--\Neven if he was just a driver.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.91,0:10:44.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So then Mr. Okida\Nmade him his chauffeur?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.20,0:10:49.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He was a\Nkindhearted person, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.67,0:10:51.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! I shouldn't be here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.33,0:10:54.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to inform\Nthe company directors!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.17,0:10:59.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Mr. Okida didn't\Nhire Tokito-{\i1}san {\i0}as a driver
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.80,0:11:02.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because he was kindhearted!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.01,0:11:04.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was making an example\Nto the other employees!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.72,0:11:07.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he really was\Na warm-hearted soul...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.64,0:11:11.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tokito! Why the hell\Nweren't you paying attention?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.40,0:11:14.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...he wouldn't have yelled\Nat him like that in public!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.02,0:11:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.40,0:11:19.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, what did you\Nand Tokito-{\i1}san {\i0}talk about?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.03,0:11:20.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You seemed to be\Nhaving a good time!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.78,0:11:23.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About Aslan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.37,0:11:25.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said that long hair cats\Ndon't handle heat well,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.91,0:11:29.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so they need air-conditioned\Nrooms to live!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.91,0:11:32.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That must be tough!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.71,0:11:36.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So if it was hot enough\Nin here to melt the chocolate,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.25,0:11:39.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that cat should've been affected.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.34,0:11:42.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But from what I saw,\Nit doesn't seem weakened at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.97,0:11:48.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna go\Ntalk to Tokito-{\i1}san {\i0}too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.81,0:11:53.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear you're actually\Na programmer?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.65,0:11:55.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard you set out\Non your own two years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.65,0:11:59.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and started a software\Ncompany with your friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.53,0:12:04.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I grow up, I wanna\Nmake computer games too!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.53,0:12:06.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.37,0:12:10.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I make business software,\Nnot games.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.83,0:12:13.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Running a company must be hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.71,0:12:15.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You went bankrupt in\Njust a year, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.13,0:12:18.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything went great at first,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.05,0:12:21.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but then a certain\Nman got in the way...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.55,0:12:27.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then he drove\Nmy friend to suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.06,0:12:31.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would that certain man\Nhappen to be Mr. Okida?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.06,0:12:37.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are all kinds\Nof things in the adult world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.44,0:12:39.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget what I just said.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.19,0:12:45.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no question that Tokito-{\i1}san\N{\i0}hated Mr. Okida enough to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.53,0:12:50.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He might've begged\Nfor another job to get revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.29,0:13:00.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Mr. Okida's heart attack was\Nintentionally caused by someone,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.09,0:13:02.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tokito-{\i1}san {\i0}would\Nbe the prime suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.01,0:13:06.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how exactly\Ncould he have done it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.68,0:13:13.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Computer intrusion?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.73,0:13:14.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.35,0:13:18.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible for a home computer\Nconnected to a phone line
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.31,0:13:21.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to infiltrate another\Nhome's computer system
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.07,0:13:24.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and change its air\Nconditioning program, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.82,0:13:26.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.28,0:13:28.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For someone well-versed\Nin that field, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.83,0:13:40.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tokito-{\i1}san {\i0}is a first-rate programmer,\Nso he's definitely well-versed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.42,0:13:44.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But simply raising the\Ntemperature couldn't kill him...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.55,0:13:47.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.72,0:13:51.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I was eating ice cream\Nearlier. I must've spilled some.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.93,0:13:56.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a slob!\NNow I have to change my socks!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.02,0:14:02.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, isn't it a little hot in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.19,0:14:03.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Crank up the AC!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.94,0:14:06.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, this is just right!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.32,0:14:08.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're young so\Nit might not affect you,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.82,0:14:12.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it's best not to make it\Ntoo much cooler than it is outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.33,0:14:15.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I once read an article about\Nhow someone had a heart attack
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.33,0:14:19.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when they entered a coffee\Nshop with the AC on too high.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.29,0:14:21.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A heart attack?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.63,0:14:26.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably because of the\Nsudden drop in temperature.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.55,0:14:28.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.18,0:14:30.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tokito-{\i1}san{\i0} warmed the room up
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.30,0:14:33.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then suddenly cooled\Nit down to cause a heart attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.77,0:14:37.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it'll be hard to find proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.60,0:14:40.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe if the program\Nwas at that man's home,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.81,0:14:43.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I doubt he would\Nactually hold on to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.02,0:14:47.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'll go check for myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.61,0:14:51.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something\NI'd like you to make for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.37,0:14:52.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have an idea, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.79,0:14:56.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's some juice.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.58,0:14:58.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.25,0:14:59.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a surprise!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.92,0:15:02.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody's ever asked\Nto come see my computer before!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.79,0:15:03.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I see it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.42,0:15:06.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.67,0:15:10.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this flake thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.47,0:15:12.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.64,0:15:15.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.14,0:15:18.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This computer's so cool!\NI wish I had one!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.60,0:15:22.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It might be too early\Nfor you to have one...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.52,0:15:25.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since you're here, want\Nto play some computer games?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.07,0:15:32.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that your car?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.78,0:15:36.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the company's,\Nbut its alarm is going off!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.49,0:15:37.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be right back!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.26,0:15:51.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Open up! No?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.47,0:15:59.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who put this here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.89,0:16:02.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was it that kid?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.28,0:16:12.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No good! It's not here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.92,0:16:29.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was playing poker\Nwith the computer!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.59,0:16:31.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won with only one pair!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.97,0:16:33.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good job, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.76,0:16:36.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm overanalyzing things!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.80,0:16:38.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was just someone's prank!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.57,0:16:44.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! How did it go, Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.02,0:16:47.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From your expression, I take it\Nyou didn't find the program?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.52,0:16:48.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.07,0:16:53.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only thing I learned was how\Nto play poker against a computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.45,0:16:54.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I dunno what to do now...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.88,0:16:59.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a cat hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.54,0:17:04.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah, I probably got it from Aslan\Nthis morning at Mr. Okida's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.21,0:17:07.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had forgotten about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.75,0:17:12.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aslan is a long-haired cat, so he'd\Nbe affected if a room got too hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.59,0:17:16.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't lay out a theory\Nunless I solve this puzzle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.34,0:17:21.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! I changed my socks earlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.97,0:17:26.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means this hair\Ncame from Tokito-{\i1}san{\i0}'s apartment...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.44,0:17:27.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.98,0:17:30.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means that flake was--
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.90,0:17:33.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Megure here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.86,0:17:35.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good to hear you\Nagain, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.82,0:17:37.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Kudo Shinichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.03,0:17:38.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Kudo-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.91,0:17:41.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I'd like you\Nto investigate immediately
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.79,0:17:44.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,about Mr. Okida's sudden death.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.25,0:17:50.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Tokito, the driver?\NUnderstood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.96,0:17:53.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0} and Ran with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.42,0:17:56.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure they'll come in handy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.05,0:17:57.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.97,0:18:03.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do I have to use\Nthis to fake my own voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.85,0:18:05.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Talk about pathetic...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.94,0:18:11.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning!\NSorry for the early intrusion!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.73,0:18:13.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,May we come in?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.36,0:18:15.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.74,0:18:17.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Computer infiltration?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.74,0:18:20.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This Kudo kid sure\Nhas a good imagination!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.45,0:18:23.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I didn't kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.16,0:18:27.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to ask you about the day\Nbefore yesterday one more time...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.79,0:18:34.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two nights ago, you put Mr. Okida\Nto bed and then immediately left, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.88,0:18:36.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.05,0:18:39.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you didn't do\Nanything out of the ordinary?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.14,0:18:41.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anything out of the ordinary?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.89,0:18:43.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.68,0:18:45.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.85,0:18:49.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm almost certain you\Ntook his cat two days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.94,0:18:52.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe his name was...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.90,0:18:53.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Aslan!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.94,0:18:55.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Aslan.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.82,0:19:00.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then yesterday you took\NAslan back to the Okida home.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.95,0:19:05.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Conan-{\i1}kun {\i0}came here yesterday,\Nsome cat hair got stuck to his feet!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.12,0:19:09.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I must've picked it up when\NI held Aslan at Mr. Okida's house
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.46,0:19:11.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then it fell off here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.46,0:19:15.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Tokito-{\i1}san{\i0}!\NThere's cat litter here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.38,0:19:20.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These are used in litter boxes,\Nright, Ran-neechan?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.47,0:19:26.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, they stick to long\Nhair cats especially easily,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.10,0:19:28.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and they fall all over the\Nplace when they walk around.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.94,0:19:32.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look! Here's another one!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.77,0:19:34.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have a cat, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.23,0:19:38.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no question\Nthat you took Aslan, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.53,0:19:41.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you take Aslan?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.95,0:19:43.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uhh--
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.91,0:19:47.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You did it because you knew\Nsomething was going to happen
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.20,0:19:49.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at the Okida house that night!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.71,0:19:51.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The entire house would\Nbecome unusually warm
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.92,0:19:53.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then suddenly cool down.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.96,0:19:56.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You love animals,\Nso you took Aslan with you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.59,0:20:00.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because he would be\Naffected and possibly even die!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.38,0:20:02.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.52,0:20:13.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're actually a\Nnice person, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.98,0:20:17.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what you did was wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.98,0:20:21.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Computers were created\Nto enrich people's lives
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.32,0:20:24.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and make them happy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.45,0:20:27.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet you used\None to kill somebody!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.24,0:20:30.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That computer's your friend, isn't it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.46,0:20:34.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means you've\Nbetrayed your own friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.75,0:20:41.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.63,0:20:44.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I almost lost a dear friend
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.64,0:20:47.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and my pride as a programmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.48,0:20:59.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My program's on this disk.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.36,0:21:04.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, I didn't\Nthink this would kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.11,0:21:06.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was going to think up\Nsomething else if it failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.49,0:21:09.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you keep\Nsomething that incriminating?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.37,0:21:14.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every program I write\Nis like a child to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.33,0:21:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't bear to get rid of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.46,0:21:25.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}. Could you tell this\NShinichi something for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.05,0:21:31.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know in how many years it'll be,\Nbut when I start my next software company
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.97,0:21:34.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd love to have him work for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.60,0:21:35.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You too, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.35,0:21:38.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right! I'll tell him!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.37,0:23:16.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinichi really beat me this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.16,0:23:18.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For my student,\Nhe sure is meddling!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.83,0:23:21.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since when am I your student?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.33,0:23:23.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.54,0:23:27.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you say you saw Shinichi\Nat Professor Agasa's place yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.88,0:23:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! And when I told him about Mr. Okida\Nhe instantly knew that it was a murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.10,0:23:35.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinichi sure is smart!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.91,0:23:37.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what I'm asking about!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.10,0:23:41.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you tell me right away?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.98,0:23:45.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know I'm worried about him!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.77,0:23:47.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, uh--
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.33,0:23:50.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is he now?\NYou know, don't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.61,0:23:52.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I--
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.61,0:23:54.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fess up!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.24,0:23:59.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get back here, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.53,0:24:05.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yes, the phone rang then...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.45,0:24:08.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0} answered it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.09,0:24:12.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! They said,\N"I'm Tatsumi's wife, of course!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.03,0:24:15.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means she was\Nstill alive at that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.65,0:24:19.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tatsumi-{\i1}sensei {\i0}was with me;\Nhis alibi is airtight.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.69,0:24:23.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And besides, the hotel\Nis ten kilometers from his home.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.15,0:24:26.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next Conan--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.65,0:24:29.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Alibi Testimony Murder Case."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.27,0:24:49.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.59,0:24:51.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cassette tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.42,0:24:54.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode is a battle against a famous lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.80,0:24:56.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.69,0:24:58.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
